# Architecture Guide

## Project Structure

```
lib/
├── core/                       # Shared infrastructure
│   ├── api/                    # API layer (Chopper, interceptors)
│   ├── domain/                 # Shared domain (Result, PaginatedList)
│   ├── presentation/providers/ # Base notifiers (BaseNotifier, PaginatedNotifier)
│   ├── providers/              # Global providers (locale, config)
│   ├── theme/                  # AppTheme
│   └── widgets/                # Reusable widgets
├── features/                   # Feature modules
│   └── <feature_name>/
│       ├── data/               # Data layer
│       ├── domain/             # Domain layer
│       └── presentation/       # Presentation layer
├── l10n/                       # Localization (ARB files)
└── main.dart                   # Entry point
```

---

## Feature Structure

Each feature follows Clean Architecture with three layers:

```
features/<feature>/
├── data/                       # DATA LAYER
│   ├── models/                 # DTOs (Data Transfer Objects)
│   │   ├── <entity>_dto.dart
│   │   ├── <entity>_dto.g.dart     # Generated
│   │   └── <feature>_enums.dart    # EnumClass definitions
│   └── <feature>_repository.dart
│
├── domain/                     # DOMAIN LAYER
│   ├── models/                 # Domain models (pure entities)
│   │   └── <entity>.dart
│   └── use_cases/              # Business logic
│       └── <action>_<entity>_use_case.dart
│
└── presentation/               # PRESENTATION LAYER
    ├── screens/
    │   └── <screen>_screen.dart
    ├── providers/
    │   ├── <feature>_provider.dart
    │   ├── <feature>_state.dart
    │   └── <feature>_state.freezed.dart  # Generated
    └── widgets/
        └── <widget>.dart
```

---

## Layer Responsibilities

### Data Layer (`data/`)

**Purpose:** Handle data access and API communication.

**Contains:**
- **DTOs:** API request/response models with serialization
- **Repositories:** Abstract data sources, convert DTOs → Domain models
- **Enums:** EnumClass definitions for API values

```dart
// data/models/user_dto.dart
class UserDto {
  final String id;
  final String name;
  // JSON serialization methods
}

// data/auth_repository.dart
class AuthRepository {
  final AuthService _service;
  
  Future<Result<User>> login(String email, String password) async {
    try {
      final dto = await _service.login(email, password);
      return Success(dto.toDomain()); // Convert DTO → Domain
    } catch (e) {
      return Failure(e.toString());
    }
  }
}
```

### Domain Layer (`domain/`)

**Purpose:** Business logic and pure domain models.

**Contains:**
- **Domain Models:** Pure entities (no serialization, no framework deps)
- **Use Cases:** Single business operations

```dart
// domain/models/user.dart
class User {
  final String id;
  final String name;
  // Pure domain model - NO JSON, NO frameworks
}

// domain/use_cases/login_user_use_case.dart
class LoginUserUseCase {
  final AuthRepository _repository;
  
  Future<Result<User>> execute(String email, String password) {
    // Business logic here
    return _repository.login(email, password);
  }
}
```

### Presentation Layer (`presentation/`)

**Purpose:** UI rendering and state management.

**Contains:**
- **Screens:** UI widgets that display data
- **Providers:** StateNotifiers that manage UI state
- **Widgets:** Feature-specific UI components

```dart
// presentation/providers/auth_provider.dart
class AuthNotifier extends StateNotifier<AuthState> {
  final LoginUserUseCase _useCase;
  
  Future<void> login(String email, String password) async {
    state = const AuthState.loading();
    final result = await _useCase.execute(email, password);
    switch (result) {
      case Success(:final data): state = AuthState.authenticated(data);
      case Failure(:final message): state = AuthState.error(message);
    }
  }
}

// presentation/screens/login_screen.dart
class LoginScreen extends ConsumerWidget {
  // UI only - delegate logic to provider
}
```

