## Local Storage Pattern

For features needing persistence (e.g., settings):

```dart
// 1. Create data model with toJson/fromJson
class SettingsModel {
  final bool notificationsEnabled;
  Map<String, dynamic> toJson() => {...};
  factory SettingsModel.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => ...;
}

// 2. Create repository with SharedPreferences
class SettingsRepository {
  final SharedPreferences _prefs;
  static const String _key = 'app_settings';
  
  SettingsModel getSettings() {
    final json = _prefs.getString(_key);
    return json != null ? SettingsModel.fromJson(jsonDecode(json)) : SettingsModel();
  }
  
  Future<void> saveSettings(SettingsModel settings) async {
    await _prefs.setString(_key, jsonEncode(settings.toJson()));
  }
}

// 3. Create provider using sharedPreferencesProvider
final settingsRepositoryProvider = Provider<SettingsRepository>((ref) {
  final prefs = ref.watch(sharedPreferencesProvider).requireValue;
  return SettingsRepository(prefs);
});
```

**Access SharedPreferences:**
```dart
// Global SharedPreferences provider (from api_config_provider.dart)
final prefs = ref.watch(sharedPreferencesProvider).requireValue;
```
